5:
Now the war's over, things have 
started settling down in the canyon, 
huh?
7: You really made a difference, Nimbus!
11:
Hmph. I just stood around while Claw 
and Albert did everything.
16: Oh, I don't know about that.
25:
A better question would be who are 
YOU? Are you the hero who ended an 
age-old war?
27:
Or are the rumors no more than 
rumors?
36:
Behind you, sonny! You're rough 
around the edges, but I'm sure I could 
make something of you boys yet.
40: W-what is that supposed to mean?
44:
We don't have time to play tag, 
gramps. Either spit out what you want 
or leave us alone.
48:
Aren't WE in a hurry?
My name's Jay. Jay Baird.
51:
I know a good cafe nearby. Let's have 
a little chat over lunch, eh?
53:
Humor me, Selenius. I haven't seen 
you in a long time, boy.
64:
Here's that extra plate of appetizers 
you ordered!
68:
Fantastic! *pat* You can put it right 
here.
72:
This is a great little spot. The food is 
amazing!
75:
Aw, it's all thanks to you guys! Business 
is booming now the war's over. We've 
been getting a ton of dogfolk curious 
about cat cuisine! Enjoy your meal!
78:
Whew, I'm stuffed! That sure hit the 
spot.
81:
Now tell us what you want. 
We came to talk, not for lunch.
84:
Oh, yes, yes, of course. Once you settle 
the check.
90:
The check? ...We aren't treating you! 
Pay for what you ate your damn self!
93:
Don't worry, Nimbus, sir! It's all on the 
house! I couldn't possibly accept coin 
from the heroes who saved the 
canyon.
97:
Nuh-uh. Alk and I are payin'â€”and so's 
this geezer. He didn't do a damn thing!
100:
Maybe I didn't, maybe I did. But either 
way, I'm not turning down this kind 
gentleman's hospitality! Let's have 
another plate!
105:
Don't you DARE use our names to 
scam a meal.
108:
Why such a sourpuss? You wouldn't 
REALLY threaten a feeble old man, 
would you?
113:
Feeble my ass. If you don't have 
money to pay for yourself, I'm kickin' 
you out before you eat any more.
116:
Kids these days! I can't believe you'd 
kick a starving old man out to the 
streets. Right, Alk?
119:
Uh... um...
Just be gentle, Nimbus, okay?
135: You! What did you just do?!
143:
Hoooo boy, looks like the spirits are on 
my side. They make my fur static-y. 
Wouldn't touch it if I were you!
145:
I'm impressed by your reflexes though. 
Seems like the apple didn't fall far from 
the tree.
154:
Just an old fart who knew your father, 
back in the day.
157:
Dunno what you mean. I don't have 
a father.
160:
You know perfectly well who I mean, 
but suit yourself.
163:
Now then, as thanks for the free meal, 
I suppose I'll join you on your travels 
and aid you.
167:
D-did you just invite yourself into our 
party?
170: We don't need a greedy old geezer!
175:
Hoo-whee. We'll see about that, won't 
we? Kick me out if you can, whipper-
snapper!
